T1  - Ambiguity Aversion and Asset Prices in Production Economies
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhu037
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 10
SP  - 3060
EP  - 3097
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine a production-based asset-pricing model with an unobservable mean growth rate following a two-state Markov chain and with an ambiguity-averse representative agent. Our model requires a low coefficient of relative risk aversion to produce: (i) a high equity premium and volatile equity returns, (ii) a low and smooth risk-free rate, (iii) smooth consumption growth and volatile investment growth, (iv) countercyclical equity premium and market price of risk, (v) conditional heteroscedasticity in returns, and (vi) long-horizon predictability of excess returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhu037
ER  - 



